When Confluence integrates with Crowd, clicking at  "Contact Administrators" link throws :

{noformat}
org.springframework.transaction.UnexpectedRollbackException: Transaction rolled back because it has been marked as rollback-only
at org.springframework.transaction.support.AbstractPlatformTransactionManager.commit(AbstractPlatformTransactionManager.java:626)
{noformat} 

That is because Confluence is looking for the group confluence-administrators :

AdministratorsAction.java - line 20:
Pager usernamesPager = userAccessor.getMemberNames(userAccessor.getGroup(UserAccessor.GROUP_CONFLUENCE_ADMINS));

A workaround for this is to  re-create  a confluence-administrators group

